<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Just an idea... Maiar should have a penalty, bringing their Prayer mod to [0.000], since it's effectively a "dead" skill for them.  <p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Prayer's still useless. Maiar cannot worship gods. It's good for (marginally) raising Spirituality/Saving Throw, but that's about it.  
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: I've removed the skill in ToME 2.3.0 (CVS) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Have I ever told you I want to bear your children? ;-) 
</p>
<p>
(Er... I am actually male, BTW :D) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: And here I was, thinking you were a Beorning..... &lt;eg&gt; 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Or Beornette... :-) 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a>: So, hm, maiar wont be able to raise their saving throw? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Good point. Maybe Maiar should get spirituality automatically (at a low mod) to ensure that they have a chance to raise this stat?  
</p>
<p>
Simon: maybe prayer and spirituality should be the same skill? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Prayer is used to cast spells from the God school (useless for a Maia), Spirituality is used to increase the saving throw, and Maia can increase it as usual. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a>: Just to ask a silly question - all classes will now get Spirituality as a raisable skill? (with the nixing of the "Abilities") 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: Yes, even Archers and Rangers (but this was a bug imo). 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a>: See <a href="./NeilStevens_2fHotaru">NeilStevens/Hotaru</a> for a sample character sheet showing a ToME 2.3 CVS polearmmaster. 
</p>
